cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with histology slide classification using convolutional neural networks. The use of multiple instance learning (MIL) and contrastive predictive coding (CPC) also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of attention-based MIL, which could place it in the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning and neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
